One of Starbucks leading challengers in China -- Luckin Coffee -- vowed on Wednesday to open 10,000 stores in the country by 2021 and expand its non-coffee sector, China Daily reported Thursday.The 22-month-old coffee house is going to add 8,000 new stores in less than three years, which means eight more stores per day on average, Qian Zhiya, CEO of Luckin Coffee, was quoted as saying by the paper.She added the company will reach 2,500 stores by the end of this year to become the country's largest coffee chain operator in terms of number of outlets and cups sold. Chinese scientists design gene-editing tool using light to kill cancer cellsAbsence at PLA maritime parade will prevent US from learning about Chinese Navy: expertsChinese American organization condemns increasing racial profiling in US Utah celebrates 150th birthday of Transcontinental RailroadActress Liu honored with Hollywood Walk of Fame star